    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-05-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-05-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="143"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d143">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_THS1">Truman</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 143 <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName corresp="#p_THS1" type="from"
                            >Truman</persName> to <persName corresp="#p_SMIV2" type="to">Marshal
                            Stalin</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d143fn1">Sent to the United States Naval Attaché, Moscow,
                        via Navy channels. Paraphrase incorporated into a note of May 29 from
                            <persName corresp="#p_HWA2">Harriman</persName> to <persName
                            corresp="#p_MVM1">Molotov</persName> for delivery to <persName
                            corresp="#p_SMIV2">Stalin</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-05-29">29 May
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Number 275, personal and top secret, from the President for Premier <persName
                        corresp="#p_SMIV2">J. V. Stalin</persName>.</p>
                <p>Thank you for your suggestion regarding surrendered German ships contained in
                    your message dated May 23, 1945.<note n="2" xml:id="d143fn2">See <ref
                            target="#d386fn2">document No. 386, footnote 2</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>It appears to me that this is an appropriate subject for discussion by the three
                    of us at the forthcoming meeting at which time I am sure a solution can be
                    reached which will be fully acceptable to all of us.</p>
                <p>Regarding the available records of the German Naval surrender it is my
                    understanding that examination of the German files is now being considered by
                    our appropriate commanders in the areas concerned.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_THS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Truman</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
